SIMPLE: contrariwise
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contrariwise
<hw>Con"tra*ri*wise</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ <?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>On the contrary; oppositely; on the other
hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not rendering evil for evil, or railing for railing; but
<qex>contrariwise</qex>, blessing.</q> <rj><qau>1 Pet. iii.
9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a contrary order; conversely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Everything that acts upon the fluids must, at the same time, act
upon the solids, and <qex>contrariwise</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrarotation</ent>⟦br⟧
